Subject: winex11: never flip a mapped window to managed

Issue #3, second half: Live's Preferences dropdown lists are its own
WS_POPUP windows, shown unmanaged (override-redirect) via SetWindowPos
with SWP_NOACTIVATE, then poked while open with an activating no-op
SetWindowPos (NOSIZE|NOMOVE|NOZORDER, no NOACTIVATE). On Windows that
call changes nothing. Here is_window_managed's "activated windows are
managed" rule made X11DRV_WindowPosChanged flip the mapped popup to
managed, and window_set_managed can only do that through a WM_STATE
unmap/remap round-trip: the open dropdown vanishes under the pointer
and comes back as a WM-managed dialog-typed toplevel. That remap is the
visible flash and the eaten first click, and the managed dialog is what
compositors then animate (mutter wobble, Dash over fullscreen), style
(Rounded Window Corners), and decorate with a shadow frame (KWin's
"second popup"). Confirmed against a live trace: WM_STATE 1 -> 0,
override-redirect 1 -> 0, WM_STATE 0 -> 1 on the open dropdown, right
after EnterNotify/MotionNotify from the user mousing over it.

Refuse the unmanaged-to-managed flip while the window is mapped: the
managed decision is made at map time, a mapped window keeps its mode
until it is withdrawn, and the next map re-evaluates. The legitimate
flip paths are unaffected: a hidden window shown activated passes (its
desired WM_STATE is still Withdrawn when the flip runs, the map request
comes later in the same SetWindowPos), make_window_embedded withdraws
explicitly before flipping, and the desktop window is created withdrawn.
window_set_managed already refuses the reverse direction outright.

The win32u menu popups (menu bar dropdowns) were never affected: they
are shown with SWP_NOACTIVATE and nothing pokes them while open, which
is why patch 0038's focus gate alone did not resolve the issue.
---
 dlls/winex11.drv/window.c | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/dlls/winex11.drv/window.c b/dlls/winex11.drv/window.c
index 9d1697d6..a92506e2 100644
--- a/dlls/winex11.drv/window.c
+++ b/dlls/winex11.drv/window.c
@@ -1890,6 +1890,20 @@ static void window_set_managed( struct x11drv_win_data *data, BOOL new_managed )
         return;
     }
 
+    /* Flipping to managed can only go through a WM_STATE unmap/remap round-trip,
+       which yanks a mapped window off the screen and hands it to the WM mid-use.
+       Live pokes its open dropdown lists with activating no-op SetWindowPos calls
+       (NOSIZE|NOMOVE|NOZORDER, no NOACTIVATE), a no-op on Windows, and the remap
+       turned the popup into a WM-managed dialog under the pointer: menus flash,
+       eat the first click, and grow WM decorations.  The managed decision is
+       made at map time; a mapped window keeps its mode until it is withdrawn,
+       and the next map re-evaluates. */
+    if (data->desired_state.wm_state != WithdrawnState)
+    {
+        WARN( "window %p/%lx is mapped, refusing to make it managed\n", data->hwnd, data->whole_window );
+        return;
+    }
+
     window_set_wm_state( data, WithdrawnState, FALSE ); /* no WM_STATE is pending, requested immediately */
 
     data->managed = new_managed;
